  # 3.2.1.83 MSS: Enable the computer to stop generating 8.3 style filenames

  <custom_item>
   type			: REGISTRY_SETTING
   description	: "3.2.1.83 MSS: Enable the computer to stop generating 8.3 style filenames: Enabled"
   info			: "In order to have backwards compatibility with 16-bit systems, it is possible to generate 8-character compatible names for every file on the system. In this case, an attacker can reference any file on the system with only 8 characters. Disable this feature to force clients to reference files by their full name."
